just follow the steps:
$ hdiutil convert -format UDRW -o destination_file.img source_file.iso $ diskutil list $ diskutil partitionDisk /dev/disk2 1 &#34;Free Space&#34; &#34;unused&#34; &#34;100%&#34; $ dd if=destination_file.img.dmg of=/dev/disk2 bs=1m note: &lsquo;disk2&rsquo; is your USB, you may need to use &lsquo;sudo dd&rsquo;
see more: bootable usb
